                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3fx74j4r/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Insurance office, &amp; I have been<lb/> told on very good authority, that he<lb/>\n                has received from them the sum<lb/> of £1200. I have earnestly spoken<lb/> to him\n                about your just claims—<lb/> he has answered me that he has<lb/> the sum of £15-3-8\n                for you in<lb/> hand which he will hand to your<lb/> order. Altho' he was insured\n                to<lb/> a large amount, he says that<lb/> if he has liquidated his own debts<lb/> he\n                shall have nothing left &amp; as<lb/> he had not received any orders<lb/> from you\n                to injure his books<lb/> in <placeName>London</placeName> he thought that you<lb/>\n                had probably insured them in <del><placeName>London</placeName></del><lb/>\n                <placeName>America</placeName>. Perhaps an<lb/> application to the Alliance\n                Insurance</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3fx74j4r/canvas/p2"
                }
